The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for affective computing, specifically in recognizing emotions within narrative materials. This falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of recurrent neural networks and transfer learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of affective computing for decision support, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
